============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/feedback.md`. Here's the summary:

**Root cause: False positive in bilingual title detection**

`"Lato | Dania główne"` (book category header: "Summer | Main dishes") sits at position 0 and is not ALL_CAPS, so it triggers the bilingual detection logic. The ALL_CAPS candidates at positions 1–2 — `"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM"` (the real title) and `"WARZYWA I BOCZEK"` — have cosine similarity > 0.4 with it because all three are Polish food-domain text. Both get suppressed from `scoredForThreshold` and consequently from `selected`.

Once the full title is gone from `selected`:
- The prefix removal step (lines 458–466) has its precondition fail (`firstStructuralHeading` not in `selected`)
- The pre-dedup section filter (lines 506–523) finds no longer parent for `"CHLEBEK"`, so it survives
- `"CHLEBEK"` (the bread sub-section header at position 8) wins by default

The previous iteration's fixes (prefix removal, pre-dedup filter) are both correct but share the same precondition: the full title must be in `selected`. The bilingual detection voids that precondition before either fix runs.
