{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BPQosyj3KvBe4RXGtQt5nX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/feedback.md`. Here's the summary:\n\n**Root cause: False positive in bilingual title detection**\n\n`\"Lato | Dania główne\"` (book category header: \"Summer | Main dishes\") sits at position 0 and is not ALL_CAPS, so it triggers the bilingual detection logic. The ALL_CAPS candidates at positions 1–2 — `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` (the real title) and `\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` — have cosine similarity > 0.4 with it because all three are Polish food-domain text. Both get suppressed from `scoredForThreshold` and consequently from `selected`.\n\nOnce the full title is gone from `selected`:\n- The prefix removal step (lines 458–466) has its precondition fail (`firstStructuralHeading` not in `selected`)\n- The pre-dedup section filter (lines 506–523) finds no longer parent for `\"CHLEBEK\"`, so it survives\n- `\"CHLEBEK\"` (the bread sub-section header at position 8) wins by default\n\nThe previous iteration's fixes (prefix removal, pre-dedup filter) are both correct but share the same precondition: the full title must be in `selected`. The bilingual detection voids that precondition before either fix runs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7171,"cache_read_input_tokens":52452,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7171},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82e232e1-70c2-44af-969c-03e475e8c638","uuid":"3f732780-5932-45e6-86a3-35263daae5ce"}
